The key insight is that the map `x ‚Ü¶ { y ‚Ü¶ ‚ąę_{z ‚ąą w} E_{a, x, y} z }` is an orthogonal projection. This is because the integral of the indicator function against the measure `E_{a, x, y}` is precisely the orthogonal projection of `y` onto the subspace `L^2(E_{a} w)`.

