The key insight is that the linear functional `f ‚Ü¶ ‚ü®x, (f(a)) y‚ü©` is equal to the integral of `f` against the measure `E_{a,x,y}`. By the properties of the Riesz-Markov-Kakutani theorem, this is an orthogonal projection.

