We need to show the function `x ‚Ü¶ ‚ąę f(z) d(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y)(z)` is continuous.

First, we need to relate the integral to the inner product. By the definition of `cfc_toComplexMeasure`, we have that for any continuous function `g`, `‚ąę g(z) d(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y)(z) = ‚ü®x, (cfcHom ha.isStarNormal g) y‚ü©_‚Ąā`.

Therefore, `fun x => (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).integral f` is equal to `fun x => ‚ü®x, (cfcHom ha.isStarNormal f) y‚ü©_‚Ąā`.

The latter function is a linear functional in `x`, and since the inner product is continuous in each variable, this function is continuous.

